        <body>
            <entry xml:id="entry_kʼona" xml:lang="os">
                <form type="lemma"><orth>kʼona</orth></form>
                <sense xml:id="sense_d3394e69"><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                        <q>очаг</q>
                    </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                        <q>fireplace</q>
                    </abv:tr></sense>
                <abv:exampleGrp>
                    <abv:example xml:id="example_d3394e81">
                        <quote>jæ mad badti ænkʼardæj arty farsmæ kʼonajyl</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>мать его (Чермена) сидела печальная у огня на очаге</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>his (Chermen's) mother was sitting sad on the hearth by the fire</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Сека._Ир._фийау"/><biblScope>25</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:id="example_d3394e100">
                        <quote>mæ kʼonajyl!</quote>
                        <note type="comment" xml:lang="ru"> (выражение страха)</note>
                        <note type="comment" xml:lang="en"> (expression of fear)</note>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Сека"/><biblScope>43</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                </abv:exampleGrp>
                <etym xml:lang="ru">Ср. в %bперсидско-курдских%b наречиях <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3394e118" xml:lang="fa" extralang="ku"><lang/>
                        <w>kuane, kuonək</w>
                        <gloss><q>очаг</q></gloss></mentioned> (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_KPF"/><biblScope xml:lang="ru">Abt. III, Bd. II, стр.
                            392</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Жуковский"/><biblScope>II 111</biblScope></bibl>). Не связаны ли эти слова с
                        <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3394e135" xml:lang="trk"><lang/>
                        <w>qonaq</w>
                        <gloss><q>дом</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3394e143" xml:lang="trk"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>ночлег</q></gloss></mentioned> и пр.? Или с <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3394e150" xml:lang="ira"><lang/>
                        <w>*kana-</w>
                        <gloss><q>жилище</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3394e158" xml:lang="ira"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>дом</q></gloss></mentioned> [<mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3394e164" xml:lang="sog"><lang/>
                        <w>*kanak(k’n’k)</w></mentioned>]?</etym>
                <etym xml:lang="en">Cf. in %bPersian-Kurdish%b dialects <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3394e172" xml:lang="fa" extralang="ku"><lang/>
                        <w>kuane, kuonək</w>
                        <gloss><q>hearth</q></gloss></mentioned> (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_KPF"/><biblScope xml:lang="en">Abt. III, Bd. II, p.
                            392</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Жуковский"/><biblScope>II 111</biblScope></bibl>). Are these words related to
                        <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3394e189" xml:lang="trk"><lang/>
                        <w>qonaq</w>
                        <gloss><q>house</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3394e197" xml:lang="trk"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>lodging for the night</q></gloss></mentioned> etc.? And are they
                    related to <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3394e204" xml:lang="ira"><lang/>
                        <w>*kana-</w>
                        <gloss><q>dwelling</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3394e212" xml:lang="ira"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>house</q></gloss></mentioned> [<mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3394e218" xml:lang="sog"><lang/>
                        <w>*kanak(k’n’k)</w></mentioned>]?</etym>
            </entry>
